---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-comparison', text: 'Coverage Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'network-and-claims', text: 'Network and Claims', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-should-choose', text: 'Who Should Choose Which', level: 2 },
  { id: 'verdict', text: 'Our Verdict', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Aetna International Review', href: '/providers/aetna-international' },
  { title: 'Best Expat Insurance', href: '/best/expat-health-insurance' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
  { key: 'aetna', header: 'Aetna International' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { feature: 'Inpatient Care', allianz: true, aetna: true },
  { feature: 'Outpatient Care', allianz: true, aetna: true },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', allianz: 'Limited', aetna: 'Moderate' },
  { feature: 'Maternity', allianz: '10-12 mo wait', aetna: '10-12 mo wait' },
  { feature: 'Dental', allianz: 'Optional', aetna: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Vision', allianz: 'Optional', aetna: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Telemedicine', allianz: true, aetna: true },
  { feature: 'Medical Evacuation', allianz: true, aetna: true },
  { feature: 'US Coverage', allianz: 'Add-on', aetna: 'Included (most plans)' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'age', header: 'Age' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
  { key: 'aetna', header: 'Aetna International' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { age: '30', allianz: '$150-240/mo', aetna: '$160-250/mo' },
  { age: '40', allianz: '$200-320/mo', aetna: '$220-340/mo' },
  { age: '50', allianz: '$270-420/mo', aetna: '$290-440/mo' },
  { age: '60', allianz: '$400-600/mo', aetna: '$420-640/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Allianz Care vs Aetna International"
  description="Compare Allianz Care and Aetna International health insurance. European value vs US-backed premium coverage for expats."
  headline="Allianz Care vs Aetna International"
  subheadline="European value player vs US-backed premium insurer. Here's how they stack up."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes from Both"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care and Aetna International represent different approaches to international health insurance. Allianz offers competitive European-headquartered coverage, while Aetna brings CVS Health backing and strong US integration.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Allianz Care</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>German-headquartered global insurer</li>
        <li>Competitive pricing (15-20% less)</li>
        <li>Strong financial backing</li>
        <li>Good for cost-conscious expats</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Aetna International</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>CVS Health backed (US)</li>
        <li>US coverage included by default</li>
        <li>CVS prescription benefits</li>
        <li>Better for Americans abroad</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Both Providers"
    description="Get personalized quotes from Allianz and Aetna."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="coverage-comparison">Coverage Comparison</h2>
  <p>
    Both offer comprehensive international coverage. The key difference is US coverage—Aetna includes it by default, while Allianz charges extra.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />
  </div>

  <p><strong>Key differences:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Aetna includes US coverage in most plans; Allianz charges 30-50% more for it</li>
    <li>Aetna has slightly better mental health coverage</li>
    <li>Allianz offers more plan customization options</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz is typically 10-15% cheaper for equivalent coverage (excluding US). If you need US coverage, the gap narrows significantly.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p><strong>Pricing notes:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Prices assume worldwide coverage excluding US for Allianz</li>
    <li>Aetna prices include US coverage</li>
    <li>Adding US to Allianz eliminates most price difference</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="network-and-claims">Network and Claims</h2>

  <h3>Provider Networks</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Allianz Care</strong> has good global coverage with direct billing at major hospitals worldwide. Network is strong in Europe and Asia.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Aetna International</strong> has excellent US network access through CVS Health integration, plus solid international coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Claims Process</h3>
  <p>
    Both offer app-based and online claims. Aetna's US integration makes claims smoother for US-based care. Allianz processes are straightforward but may be slower.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-should-choose">Who Should Choose Which</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose Allianz Care If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You don't need US coverage</li>
        <li>Budget is a primary concern</li>
        <li>You're a European expat</li>
        <li>You want plan flexibility</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose Aetna International If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You're American and need US coverage</li>
        <li>You want CVS prescription benefits</li>
        <li>You had Aetna through an employer</li>
        <li>You visit the US frequently</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    The decision often comes down to US coverage needs. If you're American or need regular US healthcare access, Aetna's integrated approach makes sense despite higher base pricing.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you don't need US coverage, Allianz offers better value with comparable international coverage. The 10-15% savings compound significantly over years of premiums.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Decide?"
    description="Get quotes from both providers for your specific situation."
    buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Prices and coverage details change. Verify all information with providers before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
